> Our play on Roman-style Saltimbocca incorporates all the best parts of this famous
> dish: crispy prosciutto, herbaceous sage, and a rich, intensely flavorful sauce.
> We've nixed the tedious prep work to give you an elegant weeknight dinner ready
> in under 30 minutes.

Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Season both sides of the @chicken breasts{2} with
@salt{pinch} and @pepper{}. Top each breast with @sage leaves{2} and tightly
wrap with two slices of @prosciutto{4%slices}. Place the prosciutto-wrapped
chicken seam side-down on a lightly oiled #baking sheet{} and place in the oven
for ~{20-25%minutes}, until juices run clear when pierced with a #knife{}.

Meanwhile, thinly slice the @garlic{2%cloves} and remaining @sage{2%leaves}.
Halve the @grape tomatoes{8}. Halve the @lemon{1}. Thinly slice the @shallot{1}.

When the chicken is half way done, heat @olive oil{1/2%tablespoon} in a
#large pan{} over medium heat. Add the garlic and cook for ~{30%seconds}, until
fragrant. Add the halved tomatoes and a squeeze of lemon and cook another
~{1-2%minutes}, until softened. Set the pan aside off the heat, we'll be adding
the spinach later!

== Pan Sauce ==

Heat @olive oil{1%tablespoon} in the #small pan{}. Add the shallot to the pan
and cook, tossing, until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add the sliced sage and cook
for ~{30%seconds} more, until fragrant. Stir in @water{1/2%cup}, a squeeze of
lemon, and the @veggie stock concentrate{1}. Simmer the sauce for
~{2-3%minutes}, until thickened. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Spinach ==

While the pan sauce simmers, add the @spinach{8%cups} to the pan with the
tomatoes and cook over low heat for ~{1-2%minutes}, until slightly wilted.
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== To Serve ==

Plate the chicken with a side of spinach and tomatoes. Drizzle with the pan
sauce and enjoy!